# Exploration: fold

## Test scope
  81 behavioral groups: 49 unique, 32 shared

  Contexts referenced below:
    words_minimal / stdin:
      write "input.txt" "aardvark\nabbreviation\nabout\nabstract\naccept\naccepted..."
      write "other.txt" "hello world"
      stdin: cherry\napple\nbanana

## Observed: 3/3 flags
  1 uniquely observable, 2 distinguishable via flag pairs
  robustness: 4 verified in all contexts, 0 in most, 0 context-dependent

Aliases: -b = --bytes, -s = --spaces, -w = --width

## Verified behavior (flag produced observable output)
  -w  # use WIDTH columns instead of 80
    tested: "--width=2" in words_minimal / stdin
    | flag adds 9 lines: ch, er, ry, ap, pl
    | flag removes 3 lines: cherry, apple, banana
    without flag:
      cherry
      apple
      banana
    with flag:
      ch
      er
      ry
      ap
      pl
      e
            ... (3 more)

## Distinguishable in combination (verified via flag pairs)
  -b  # count bytes rather than columns
    | exit: 1 → 0
    | stderr removed
    proven via: (pairwise evidence)
  -s  # break at spaces
    | exit: 1 → 0
    | stderr removed
    proven via: (pairwise evidence)

